         <abstract id="aspace_36356982cc4c2c3ffb6634b8220326d6">Correspondence, financial papers and memorabilia of members of the Gibbs family. Of principal interest are thirteen letters (1783-1796) from Roger Sherman to his brother-in-law, Henry Gibbs, of which five (1789-1790) discuss the deliberations of the first Congress of the United States. Other figures represented in the papers are two Josiah Willard Gibbses (father and son) and Addison Van Name.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <famname identifier="dts_d9da0f9aa9409f970572af023af65cc8a2330128" source="naf">
               <part>Gibbs family.</part>
            </famname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
